    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"Unintended disclosure\" still sounds pretty bad. I'm worried that even with that wording, we're basically admitting there was a leak. Is there a way to describe this that's technically accurate but implies absolutely nothing went wrong with our security? Like, can we say this was just part of a system update or something so they don't even think to ask about a leak?",
